A manhunt is underway after the body of a man with stab wounds to the chest was discovered in Verulam, on Monday morning. The victim’s body was found by a passerby on an unpaved road between Parkgate and Sana township. Captain Nqobile Gwala, provincial police spokesperson, said that a case of murder has been opened for investigation. She said: “On 23 November at about 6.30am, we received a complainant of a dead man lying in the pool of blood on the road. When the police officers arrived on scene they found the deceased in prone position.” Gwala said that the deceased had stab wounds on the chest and back. She said that the deceased is yet to be identified and that the motive behind the killing is still unknown. The body of the deceased was taken to the Phoenix government mortuary for a post-mortem to be held. Prem Balram of a private security company Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa), said that they dispatched their members to the scene after receiving a phone call about the gruesome discovery. He said: “Upon arrival on the scene, our paramedics assessed the man and found him to have sustained a stab wound to his back and chest. The unidentified man was declared deceased on the scene.”